x id="143"/><x id="144"/><x id="145"/><x id="146"/></source><seg-source><x id="131"/><mrk mtype="seg" mid="47"><x id="132"/><g id="142"><g id="135">578	</g><g id="141">Gutowski</g></g><x id="143"/><x id="144"/><x id="145"/><x id="146"/></mrk></seg-source><target><x id="131"/><mrk mtype="seg" mid="47"/></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="47"><sdl:rep id="QKiSsA+axNBEuutGYcp7vPPD2PN4jnH9H0PlpgZb/AY="/><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">QKiSsA+axNBEuutGYcp7vPPD2PN4jnH9H0PlpgZb/AY=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="35"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="23a86fb7-cb52-4021-bdf5-340bba945539"><source><g id="166"><g id="153"><g id="149">The   Ulthera   system   delivers   transcutaneous MFU  energy  from  an  operator-controlled  hand piece (</g><g id="152">Fig. 1</g><g id="156">) and a monitor allows direct visualiza-tion (</g><g id="159">Fig. 2</g><g id="162">) of where the energy will be delivered so that specific structures such as bone can be avoided.</g></g><g id="153"><g id="162">  </g></g><g id="153"><g id="162">The  focal  energy  delivery  in  given  in predetermined “lines” results in discrete intervals between 1 mm</g></g><g id="170"><g id="165">3  </g><g id="169">coagulation zones that promote healing.</g></g></g></source><seg-source><g id="166"><g id="153"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="48"><g id="149">The   Ulthera   system   delivers   transcutaneous MFU  energy  from  an  operator-controlled  hand piece (</g><g id="152">Fig. 1</g><g id="156">) and a monitor allows direct visualiza-tion (</g><g id="159">Fig. 2</g><g id="162">) of where the energy will be delivered so that specific structures such as bone can be avoided.</g></mrk></g><g id="153"><g id="162">  </g></g><mrk mtype="seg" mid="49"><g id="153"><g id="162">The  focal  energy  delivery  in  given  in predetermined “lines” results in discrete intervals between 1 mm</g></g><g id="170"><g id="165">3  </g><g id="169">coagulation zones that promote healing.</g></g></mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="166"><g id="153"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="48"/></g><g id="153"><g id="162">  </g></g><mrk mtype="seg" mid="49"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="48"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">4zLY2yeD7N5rBrqIjKHmVRVe00cPNTW+cQ0xNHF+Lj4=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="49"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">4nJ5TfjGBbw4n1Enet7EEP9G6WgLwKAa0uACuMmXVHg=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="36"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="5c5d6e91-b681-4c07-938c-e70c07ff5f31"><source><g id="173">INDICATIONS</g></source><seg-source><g id="173"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="50">INDICATIONS</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="173"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="50"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="50"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">j/EJP6gcKRnd5uzLyYGMuw1Mi1SeYLmOS2Pu/ueghvw=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="37"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="5d08bceb-c8cb-49a5-9e82-9c8fa2f53800"><source><g id="176">Although  the  currently  approved  indications  are listed  below,  other  facial  and  nonfacial  areas have been treated:</g></source><seg-source><g id="176"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="51">Although  the  currently  approved  indications  are listed  below,  other  facial  and  nonfacial  areas have been treated:</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="176"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="51"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="51"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">f4ZFj2QVJHwISY3yIhO2s1eB9Aszsq+vx+pYa5jbRm4=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="38"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="6e7e4a64-6653-4358-ba8b-31652e64a140"><source><g id="179">  Lift eyebrows</g></source><seg-source><g id="179">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="52">Lift eyebrows</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="179">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="52"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="52"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">6ZieUrrWjN3kAEXyCc4MZhPpvUsK7F7LRtdSQl9CvTU=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="39"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="b252413c-5304-4be8-946f-aa84c549c22f"><source><x id="189"/><g id="192">  Lift submental tissue (chin and neck)</g></source><seg-source><mrk mtype="seg" mid="53"><x id="189"/><g id="192">  Lift submental tissue (chin and neck)</g></mrk></seg-source><target><mrk mtype="seg" mid="53"/></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="53"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">PV/ZAQGFn+m9xhN8X7jdfe/0aIdRJYta3/M+HErbOsM=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="40"/><sdl:cxt id="4"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="ce02c7fe-cb92-4ce0-a72c-0d051e91e84f"><source><g id="182">´	´</g></source><seg-source><g id="182"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="54">´	´</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="182"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="54"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="54"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">eRyaaDxb/WqyYUngK13RYc0n4dkku/VvrgQuUpXWEqc=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="41"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="cfd60f05-f641-430b-a6ce-d0afa3296747"><source><g id="195">  Improve lines and wrinkles in decollete</g></source><seg-source><g id="195">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="55">Improve lines and wrinkles in decollete</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="195">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="55"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="55"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">HcsdjB1J9zXwzWrhbeB6UNzi9w8ZsMU2owk3Q1WVaVA=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="42"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="9e079013-56e8-461e-b3f0-8a8a737b7b91"><source><g id="198">HISTOLOGIC STUDIES</g></source><seg-source><g id="198"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="56">HISTOLOGIC STUDIES</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="198"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="56"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="56"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">E0Or3pDa1f0ZW82cFJ/mOLj+v0WxFtghfo9WGb7wfAk=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="43"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="60ac83ee-d6e3-43cb-b828-bd814fdb8d65"><source><g id="205"><g id="201">An  early  prototype  Ulthera  device  was  used  on the  lateral  cheek  region  in  patients  who  would be   undergoing   a   surgical   rhytidectomy   within 12  weeks  of  treatment.</g><g id="204">3   </g><g id="208">Skin  histology  showed consistent and reproducible thermal injury zones in  the  dermis,  without  injury  to  the  epidermis, which was absent by 12 weeks.</g><g id="208"> </g><g id="208">Another study</g><g id="211">4 </g><g id="214">showed  more  dermal  collagen  in  the  reticular dermis (24% increase) 2 months after treatment resulting  in  a  mean  increase  in  dermal  thick-ening from 1.32 to 1.63 mm. Elastic fibers of the upper and lower dermis were more parallel and straighter.</g></g></source><seg-source><g id="205"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="57"><g id="201">An  early  prototype  Ulthera  device  was  used  on the  lateral  cheek  region  in  patients  who  would be   undergoing   a   surgical   rhytidectomy   within 12  weeks  of  treatment.</g><g id="204">3   </g><g id="208">Skin  histology  showed consistent and reproducible thermal injury zones in  the  dermis,  without  injury  to  the  epidermis, which was absent by 12 weeks.</g></mrk><g id="208"> </g><mrk mtype="seg" mid="58"><g id="208">Another study</g><g id="211">4 </g><g id="214">showed  more  dermal  collagen  in  the  reticular dermis (24% increase) 2 months after treatment resulting  in  a  mean  increase  in  dermal  thick-ening from 1.32 to 1.63 mm. Elastic fibers of the upper and lower dermis were more parallel and straighter.</g></mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="205"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="57"/><g id="208"> </g><mrk mtype="seg" mid="58"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="57"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">YNkg42qq3T9FXL5ueNcYOpq7kolqaw2JQlNg31hZcq8=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="58"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">i8Mm54QZ3G+Lani8ATI5U5DoCkWgtB+WyEy7ulVv/MY=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="44"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="be09c258-ff84-485a-a21f-392a6cb33276"><source><g id="217">TREATMENT TIMES</g></source><seg-source><g id="217"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="59">TREATMENT TIMES</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="217"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="59"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="59"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">+G96D4aAGcf01zzEFo7XfqK5ev+uEGEqseh4XGZb8nE=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="45"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="6a0b1db7-e014-4ae8-832b-5337bd15d915"><source><g id="220">Treatment  times  for  the  full  face  and  neck  are generally less than 90 minutes, but vary depend-ing  on  provider  experience,  aggressiveness  of</g></source><seg-source><g id="220"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="60">Treatment  times  for  the  full  face  and  neck  are generally less than 90 minutes, but vary depend-ing  on  provider  experience,  aggressiveness  of</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="220"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="60"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="60"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">AV9b6nHibsBAjHb4E4+BxEt/1Ay6jLnuUhG5ZGES/UQ=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="46"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="0b36a0e4-9b54-4d1b-a61c-88da60c5f10b"><source><g id="227"><g id="223">Fig. 1.  </g><g id="226">Patient treatment with Ulthera microfocused ultrasound hand piece.</g></g></source><seg-source><g id="227"><g id="223"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="61">Fig. 1.</mrk>  </g><g id="226"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="62">Patient treatment with Ulthera microfocused ultrasound hand piece.</mrk></g></g></seg-source><target><g id="227"><g id="223"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="61"/>  </g><g id="226"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="62"/></g></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="61"><sdl:rep id="LjHbAc+m+xVrLWU5bTE2pGR6uBtWi12RCfNGOOp/WYA="/><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">LjHbAc+m+xVrLWU5bTE2pGR6uBtWi12RCfNGOOp/WYA=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="62"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">w4QRIzlzmaEzmYtbDqAnhIFw+qQhm1VCsFAhaYbcVdQ=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="47"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="10b7c099-175d-46d2-87ed-6913d1f1b4e9"><source><x id="228"/><g id="231">protocol, patient comfort, and treatment surface area.</g></source><seg-source><mrk mtype="seg" mid="63"><x id="228"/><g id="231">protocol, patient comfort, and treatment surface area.</g></mrk></seg-source><target><mrk mtype="seg" mid="63"/></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="63"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">yuOOkuHUutW/doh2oErYY+cVLNteaYK3Gq9M09BdU60=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="48"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="f33cf375-1194-4b91-b726-6aad7dd1f2b4"><source><g id="234">  Face – 30 to 60 minutes   Neck – 30 to 45 minutes</g></source><seg-source><g id="234">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="64">Face – 30 to 60 minutes   Neck – 30 to 45 minutes</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="234">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="64"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="64"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">8DVhKn/gEwW3QtZc3KdVH62VwY1UhhvfLIkV3umDjhg=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="49"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="1c0b6bcb-1409-4150-b6b4-2960866ad4f3"><source><g id="237">PRETREATMENT</g></source><seg-source><g id="237"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="65">PRETREATMENT</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="237"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="65"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="65"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">BnsBn7IZBQ5GAyPx+dRQ4DL7qkN57hA2W8FOHPD8F7I=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="50"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="d67cfd84-46a0-4053-9d63-2de09e3d5c87"><source><g id="244"><g id="240">  </g><g id="240">Topical  betacaine/lidocaine/procaine  cream for 60 minutes</g><g id="243">5</g></g></source><seg-source><g id="244"><g id="240">  </g><mrk mtype="seg" mid="66"><g id="240">Topical  betacaine/lidocaine/procaine  cream for 60 minutes</g><g id="243">5</g></mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="244"><g id="240">  </g><mrk mtype="seg" mid="66"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="66"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">uqxchpRSdgFE/0egTaISheET1bKPodYyuh6rLLmEvW0=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="51"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="1f02de2e-5479-44d3-8b7a-dc5907f1194a"><source><g id="251"><g id="247">  </g><g id="247">Topical    lidocaine/tetracaine    (7%/7%)    for 45 minutes</g><g id="250">6</g></g></source><seg-source><g id="251"><g id="247">  </g><mrk mtype="seg" mid="67"><g id="247">Topical    lidocaine/tetracaine    (7%/7%)    for 45 minutes</g><g id="250">6</g></mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="251"><g id="247">  </g><mrk mtype="seg" mid="67"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="67"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">3LvQR6p6FDybMLt3os/gRF5vMaqw2G+nBmkKTrS7LDM=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="52"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="f00d4a87-9cb2-4eb9-97e0-f3396787e054"><source><g id="258"><g id="254">SPECIFIC APPLICATIONS </g><g id="257">Face and Neck</g></g></source><seg-source><g id="258"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="68"><g id="254">SPECIFIC APPLICATIONS </g><g id="257">Face and Neck</g></mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="258"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="68"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="68"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">lGo3q2oeizqeNtEjOv/m9qt4N1M8/oL1i1/4P0159IA=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="53"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="2c5b1410-cefc-4f0c-8f8d-0ce118e33abc"><source><g id="265"><g id="261">A prospective rater-blinded study of the forehead, temples,  cheeks,  submental  region,  and  side  of neck  measured  outcomes  at  90  days.</g><g id="264">6   </g><g id="268">Probes used  were  4  MHz,  4.5-mm  focal  depth  (source energy 0.75–1.2 J), 7 MHz, 4.5-mm  focal  depth (source energy 0.75–1.05 J), and 7 MHz, 3.0-mm focal depth (source energy 0.4–0.63 J).</g><g id="268"> Ultrasound pulses  were  administered  every  1.5  mm  along each treatment line with 3 to 5 mm between treat-ment lines. Thirty of 35 patients (86%) had a clini-cally  significant  improvement  in  brow  elevation (mean, 1.7 mm). Unfortunately, the imaging used in the study design did not allow for conclusions to be made regarding improvement of other treat-ment areas.</g></g></source><seg-source><g id="265"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="69"><g id="261">A prospective rater-blinded study of the forehead, temples,  cheeks,  submental  region,  and  side  of neck  measured  outcomes  at  90  days.</g><g id="264">6   </g><g id="268">Probes used  were  4  MHz,  4.5-mm  focal  depth  (source energy 0.75–1.2 J), 7 MHz, 4.5-mm  focal  depth (source energy 0.75–1.05 J), and 7 MHz, 3.0-mm focal depth (source energy 0.4–0.63 J).</g></mrk><g id="268"> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="70">Ultrasound pulses  were  administered  every  1.5  mm  along each treatment line with 3 to 5 mm between treat-ment lines.</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="71">Thirty of 35 patients (86%) had a clini-cally  significant  improvement  in  brow  elevation (mean, 1.7 mm).</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="72">Unfortunately, the imaging used in the study design did not allow for conclusions to be made regarding improvement of other treat-ment areas.</mrk></g></g></seg-source><target><g id="265"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="69"/><g id="268"> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="70"/> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="71"/> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="72"/></g></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="69"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">7HIAGGJGUIa8DZVf6VSiyktoGeOUfDcXKgErVQ81Pfk=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="70"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">VUyJl9NM9SRdzn1LNotvzAZIq3GBRU2C5/2Vdec0jUI=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="71"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">aF3JHMSz1ENTDcbv9aMH2lcwc9NrKvi+y2se0KE5eUY=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="72"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">N8sN6anIG79hstHzR4Ov463SyWHX2x0XHlrEBFkHOBY=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="54"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="ca2a5718-4e12-4352-8bc4-a7cc94774555"><source><g id="271">Periorbital Region</g></source><seg-source><g id="271"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="73">Periorbital Region</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="271"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="73"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="73"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">pXqQEDwPACb+1jGqRM9ej/7agjrSM+Ej6iqwEj+SJoo=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="55"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="df549e8b-90ad-4ec0-85b7-bda40dbf0a09"><source><g id="274">As with any energy device, extreme care is needed when  treating  the  thinner  periocular  skin.  Direct treatment of eyelids over the eye itself is not indi-cated.  Upper  eyelid  improvement  can  be  seen after treatment of the forehead and brow owing to brow elevation.</g></source><seg-source><g id="274"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="74">As with any energy device, extreme care is needed when  treating  the  thinner  periocular  skin.</mrk>  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="75">Direct treatment of eyelids over the eye itself is not indi-cated.</mrk>  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="76">Upper  eyelid  improvement  can  be  seen after treatment of the forehead and brow owing to brow elevation.</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="274"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="74"/>  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="75"/>  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="76"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="74"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">W3/O0hUQFRqyx8X951BsjM24OHBqfwHHJMpPhIao488=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="75"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">JKYwJ2WeeMQLqMfLZwarMdedGgfRQakfl7oOJI++nWY=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="76"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">VRcNHBxtUPNAcLMZrnBKgMODklWwasG5jd6Vq7xC3bs=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="56"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="32652a6f-68dc-4980-b85b-f579d7cb40d2"><source><g id="281"><g id="277">Two studies of lower eyelid treatments, both in Asian patients, showed improvement in infraorbital laxity.</g><g id="277">  </g><g id="277">Quantitative  improvement  was  seen  after targeting the lower eyelid skin and orbital septum with 1.5-mm and 3.0-mm probes in a small series of 7 patients.</g><g id="280">6 </g><g id="284">A larger study of 15 patients</g><g id="287">7,8 </g><g id="290">also showed improvement in most patients.</g><g id="290"> Histologic analysis confirmed increased collagen and elastin fibers  in  the  reticular  dermis,  but  there  was  no significant change in the epidermis.</g></g></source><seg-source><g id="281"><g id="277"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="77">Two studies of lower eyelid treatments, both in Asian patients, showed improvement in infraorbital laxity.</mrk></g><g id="277">  </g><mrk mtype="seg" mid="78"><g id="277">Quantitative  improvement  was  seen  after targeting the lower eyelid skin and orbital septum with 1.5-mm and 3.0-mm probes in a small series of 7 patients.</g><g id="280">6 </g><g id="284">A larger study of 15 patients</g><g id="287">7,8 </g><g id="290">also showed improvement in most patients.</g></mrk><g id="290"> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="79">Histologic analysis confirmed increased collagen and elastin fibers  in  the  reticular  dermis,  but  there  was  no significant change in the epidermis.</mrk></g></g></seg-source><target><g id="281"><g id="277"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="77"/></g><g id="277">  </g><mrk mtype="seg" mid="78"/><g id="290"> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="79"/></g></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="77"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">z0p1xgdBh+OTeqb0eDPE6ZLgDtT44oGF9M9OHol4SUg=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="78"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">cs6EXebE1R3Sg3gyEzQuv7AkUip45cMuHZSp1wChujo=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="79"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">3Zu6yfRt9lrBUYjoQb7oNeJZM6jtfy3saiLv+uZwp+o=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="57"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="faa1f78f-8b8a-4031-aef4-645b70e2fdb8"><source><g id="293">Nasolabial Folds and Jaw Line</g></source><seg-source><g id="293"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="80">Nasolabial Folds and Jaw Line</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="293"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="80"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="80"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">8CZ5O6YFvBQwtA6ory61J3crdZPR8wcGOhWOc0JqQ8c=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="58"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="38c3da70-4f42-4e29-97e5-f61d964bcf8a"><source><g id="300"><g id="296">A   prospective,   blinded   evaluator   study   of   22 patients  using  7.5-  and  4.4-MHz  hand  pieces, delivering  energy  to  a  focal  depth  of  3.0  and 4.5  mm  with  linear  arrays  spaced  in  parallel  at 3  mm,  evaluated  the  nasolabial  folds  and  jaw line.</g><g id="299">4  </g><g id="303">Two months after treatment of the face and</g></g></source><seg-source><g id="300"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="81"><g id="296">A   prospective,   blinded   evaluator   study   of   22 patients  using  7.5-  and  4.4-MHz  hand  pieces, delivering  energy  to  a  focal  depth  of  3.0  and 4.5  mm  with  linear  arrays  spaced  in  parallel  at 3  mm,  evaluated  the  nasolabial  folds  and  jaw line.</g><g id="299">4  </g><g id="303">Two months after treatment of the face and</g></mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="300"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="81"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="81"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">LIIBFIePdmB64dUOgdmOvtBLSiPMkgFVYOLa/x5F8y4=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="59"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="8fb8f918-ed4e-4221-a9d5-a159c54374f1"><source><g id="306">Downloaded for Anonymous User (n/a) at Seoul National University Hospital from ClinicalKey.com by Elsevier on July 27, 2023. For personal use only. No other uses without permission. Copyright ©2023. Elsevier Inc. All rights reserved.</g><x id="307"/></source><seg-source><g id="306"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="82">Downloaded for Anonymous User (n/a) at Seoul National University Hospital from ClinicalKey.com by Elsevier on July 27, 2023.</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="83">For personal use only.</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="84">No other uses without permission.</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="85">Copyright ©2023.</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="86">Elsevier Inc. All rights reserved.</mrk></g><x id="307"/></seg-source><target><g id="306"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="82"/> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="83"/> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="84"/> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="85"/> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="86"/></g><x id="307"/></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="82"><sdl:rep id="mTircHggKyN0qYacONQdEAcyLynKpWXg+eutC8ezjvI="/><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">mTircHggKyN0qYacONQdEAcyLynKpWXg+eutC8ezjvI=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="83"><sdl:rep id="apFJZlrHl140uoajSp2UIdNk88J2FSPtQVN3Gsm8Z/8="/><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">apFJZlrHl140uoajSp2UIdNk88J2FSPtQVN3Gsm8Z/8=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="84"><sdl:rep id="P3yAfTJ3Db4SFDuoEejStQdX0TywfhOhIcA9JmgaltM="/><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">P3yAfTJ3Db4SFDuoEejStQdX0TywfhOhIcA9JmgaltM=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="85"><sdl:rep id="UtaULUqG/A/LJLccCi54FYXwHaD9yQDeWghC7okUl/c="/><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">UtaULUqG/A/LJLccCi54FYXwHaD9yQDeWghC7okUl/c=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="86"><sdl:rep id="ebZCJya3RmLgEZAXDuPo359W5RHKGXhy1Hb6+bl3SnY="/><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">ebZCJya3RmLgEZAXDuPo359W5RHKGXhy1Hb6+bl3SnY=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="60"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="07693dee-e199-41cf-8872-3ea238bb9194"><source><x id="308"/><x id="309"/><g id="319"><g id="312">Microfocused Ultrasound for Skin Tightening	</g><g id="318">579</g></g><x id="320"/><x id="321"/><x id="322"/><x id="323"/></source><seg-source><x id="308"/><mrk mtype="seg" mid="87"><x id="309"/><g id="319"><g id="312">Microfocused Ultrasound for Skin Tightening	</g><g id="318">579</g></g><x id="320"/><x id="321"/><x id="322"/><x id="323"/></mrk></seg-source><target><x id="308"/><mrk mtype="seg" mid="87"/></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="87"><sdl:rep id="j+A08L+4G/xtXwALuYZ/RZcoqtLI9bpgvaQrb+YUjZQ="/><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">j+A08L+4G/xtXwALuYZ/RZcoqtLI9bpgvaQrb+YUjZQ=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="61"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="f7249d01-a09f-4bc8-bfbc-2445590c5eef"><source><g id="330"><g id="326">Fig. 2.  </g><g id="329">Ulthera screen display. The upper one-third of the screen shows the depth of tissue treatment.</g></g></source><seg-source><g id="330"><g id="326"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="88">Fig. 2.</mrk>  </g><g id="329"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="89">Ulthera screen display.</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="90">The upper one-third of the screen shows the depth of tissue treatment.</mrk></g></g></seg-source><target><g id="330"><g id="326"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="88"/>  </g><g id="329"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="89"/> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="90"/></g></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="88"><sdl:rep id="LjHbAc+m+xVrLWU5bTE2pGR6uBtWi12RCfNGOOp/WYA="/><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">LjHbAc+m+xVrLWU5bTE2pGR6uBtWi12RCfNGOOp/WYA=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="89"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">jvY6Rd0pyE8FtwLspDEqY/j0TQ2IlTjST2zqGSvFKus=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="90"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">q62/n+H5MS15obiT82MdXsDue1wLLSpfNtFZ4KwLPkY=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="62"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="e10f6a81-a933-4c59-a561-bd0d93445011"><source><g id="333">submental area, all patients demonstrated nasola-bial fold and jaw line improvement, 77% and 73% of patients subjectively reported “much improve-ment,” respectively.</g></source><seg-source><g id="333"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="91">submental area, all patients demonstrated nasola-bial fold and jaw line improvement, 77% and 73% of patients subjectively reported “much improve-ment,” respectively.</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="333"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="91"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="91"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">jeYHnx/u9QKmpBTkkiluRiy1X3Mnf29r3qcV4XFqlLI=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="63"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="ff0b1105-2c08-47d8-af3f-3e2520cc0584"><source><g id="336">Superficial Musculoaponeurotic System</g></source><seg-source><g id="336"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="92">Superficial Musculoaponeurotic System</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="336"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="92"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="92"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">ejmelNqerWAgCFpUFHRdg4wgvY3sEZTD57xkRkdWf+0=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="64"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="2cd121fa-397d-40ae-8b15-313906101793"><source><g id="343"><g id="339">A   cadaver   study   of   transcutaneous   Ulthera energy delivery in the face demonstrated thermal injury   zones   in   the   SMAS   along   with   SMAS contraction proportional to the amount of energy delivered.</g><g id="342">9  </g><g id="346">The epidermis and sub-SMAS struc-tures  were  not  affected.</g><g id="346">  These  findings  sug-gest  that  not  only  dermal  contraction,  but  also deeper  support  structural  improvement  contrib-utes  to  the  aesthetic  improvements  seen  after treatment.</g></g></source><seg-source><g id="343"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="93"><g id="339">A   cadaver   study   of   transcutaneous   Ulthera energy delivery in the face demonstrated thermal injury   zones   in   the   SMAS   along   with   SMAS contraction proportional to the amount of energy delivered.</g><g id="342">9  </g><g id="346">The epidermis and sub-SMAS struc-tures  were  not  affected.</g></mrk><g id="346">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="94">These  findings  sug-gest  that  not  only  dermal  contraction,  but  also deeper  support  structural  improvement  contrib-utes  to  the  aesthetic  improvements  seen  after treatment.</mrk></g></g></seg-source><target><g id="343"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="93"/><g id="346">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="94"/></g></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="93"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">bcaJfNhlA2cTrvKH0dXtA2zyHR68qmF5Xxi2676r2Fs=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="94"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">3XN2jzEH6PwtHgXwPf4AaKw6ugb0bcJyLSu0r/h8rKs=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="65"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="91016e24-d5c6-461b-b0e0-61264a0bf001"><source><g id="349">Buttocks</g></source><seg-source><g id="349"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="95">Buttocks</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="349"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="95"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="95"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">BdsP2M0aU8CDI6NB8L+7O7KAqsa/P5KuSh7DYrz0PFA=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="66"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="42a933ba-d7ab-4e63-92be-616448fa2f8c"><source><g id="356"><g id="352">A single study evaluated ultrasound skin tightening and smoothing of the buttocks.</g><g id="355">5 </g><g id="359">Using transducers with  3.0-  and  4.5-mm  focal  depths,  an  area  of twenty-five 1-inch by 1-inch squares was treated.</g><g id="359"> The mean number of treatment lines delivered to the right buttock was 973 (the left buttock served as a control). In most cases, the highest energy</g></g></source><seg-source><g id="356"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="96"><g id="352">A single study evaluated ultrasound skin tightening and smoothing of the buttocks.</g><g id="355">5 </g><g id="359">Using transducers with  3.0-  and  4.5-mm  focal  depths,  an  area  of twenty-five 1-inch by 1-inch squares was treated.</g></mrk><g id="359"> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="97">The mean number of treatment lines delivered to the right buttock was 973 (the left buttock served as a control).</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="98">In most cases, the highest energy</mrk></g></g></seg-source><target><g id="356"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="96"/><g id="359"> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="97"/> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="98"/></g></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="96"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">ujXbvz5DOYWpP/Ejr+NqMZJ9pccIt6tgeP+tTf7Uve4=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="97"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">rY//onciz4zhUROGa1ITKZLFoeE5lnoDjOik6P76DI8=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="98"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">0LFAPtEGuHtZVyJiQJLEbK1Pv1pJou4117szRUZujjk=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="67"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="3b56b67a-b981-42ac-b927-e102363e8273"><source><x id="360"/><g id="363">levels were not used owing to patient preference.</g><g id="363"> Standardized   blinded   assessment   and   patient satisfaction  was  measured.</g><g id="363">  Although  17  of  19 patients (89%) showed objective improvement at 180 days, only 68% expressed overall satisfaction and  most  would  not  recommend  it  to  family  or friends.</g><g id="363"> Furthermore, pain scores were high and may have limited the amount of energy delivered to the treatment area.</g><g id="363"> It is possible that improved treatmentprotocolsandpatientselectionmayyield better results.</g></source><seg-source><mrk mtype="seg" mid="99"><x id="360"/><g id="363">levels were not used owing to patient preference.</g></mrk><g id="363"> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="100">Standardized   blinded   assessment   and   patient satisfaction  was  measured.</mrk></g><g id="363">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="101">Although  17  of  19 patients (89%) showed objective improvement at 180 days, only 68% expressed overall satisfaction and  most  would  not  recommend  it  to  family  or friends.</mrk></g><g id="363"> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="102">Furthermore, pain scores were high and may have limited the amount of energy delivered to the treatment area.</mrk></g><g id="363"> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="103">It is possible that improved treatmentprotocolsandpatientselectionmayyield better results.</mrk></g></seg-source><target><mrk mtype="seg" mid="99"/><g id="363"> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="100"/></g><g id="363">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="101"/></g><g id="363"> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="102"/></g><g id="363"> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="103"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="99"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">89tJ2NwDqdorXGkk5uMNBpaed3H2bpDIaZtPfzG092c=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="100"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">Qnd9G6rfY4YNcaJaYIZ4hTFFRHwgCCSs1etnln61g1E=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="101"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">eIOWFAAlaJeBaAwrTzOPXTyBbah9MwGikcjBZrLQBag=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="102"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">Sn/qyUNxzUMXiD6doAHqhVbaoiRJrKWsMUD/gGJFT/4=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="103"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">+EUx1EJXH6i5/gCFDrkBL3EJSNyheL9TU8+IqwhqzMk=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="68"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="38093621-b585-4e10-9fc4-25d7ee806ff8"><source><g id="366">Arms, Thigh, and Knee Skin</g></source><seg-source><g id="366"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="104">Arms, Thigh, and Knee Skin</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="366"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="104"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="104"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">v9VnhXjohvXjC3MtkUKl3wzpftiRhXoHTTewWDO8M4w=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="69"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="7460b847-e5d3-40d5-8446-8ab33ac27f0e"><source><g id="373"><g id="369">Because  skin  aging  is  not  limited  to  the  face, patients(usuallywomen)commonlyseek skintight-ening of the upper arms, inner thighs, and the area just above the knees.</g><g id="369"> </g><g id="369">One small study included 6 of each of these areas using 1 (single plane) or 2 (dual treatment depths) treatment passes.</g><g id="372">10  </g><g id="376">After 6 months, blinded assessors found more skin lifting effect in the upper arms and knees than in the inner thighs.</g><g id="376"> The dual treatment depth areas had slightly better   clinical   improvement   scores.   Eighty-one percent of patients were highly satisfied and all pa-tients opted to have more treatments at the same site or at other sites. Despite the reported favorable</g></g></source><seg-source><g id="373"><g id="369"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="105">Because  skin  aging  is  not  limited  to  the  face, patients(usuallywomen)commonlyseek skintight-ening of the upper arms, inner thighs, and the area just above the knees.</mrk></g><g id="369"> </g><mrk mtype="seg" mid="106"><g id="369">One small study included 6 of each of these areas using 1 (single plane) or 2 (dual treatment depths) treatment passes.</g><g id="372">10  </g><g id="376">After 6 months, blinded assessors found more skin lifting effect in the upper arms and knees than in the inner thighs.</g></mrk><g id="376"> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="107">The dual treatment depth areas had slightly better   clinical   improvement   scores.</mrk>   <mrk mtype="seg" mid="108">Eighty-one percent of patients were highly satisfied and all pa-tients opted to have more treatments at the same site or at other sites.</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="109">Despite the reported favorable</mrk></g></g></seg-source><target><g id="373"><g id="369"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="105"/></g><g id="369"> </g><mrk mtype="seg" mid="106"/><g id="376"> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="107"/>   <mrk mtype="seg" mid="108"/> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="109"/></g></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="105"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">z4n3PBEAybgXcCZ++5JEoP7W/hMQ2Q1gb4AQHEs4slI=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="106"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">Cu2/JANJsPOMmVJH2fod5yBVzFiMGN6/DLmB5bKQBeU=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="107"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">2C+osmOBkcUnRMXe8X+aBufA5/LwDVwWaih23+ZjHJ4=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="108"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">ZyKSHXpsdVnTYe2ufdWB3xEAsD82jT94/gkzZ/Of5PM=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="109"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">lAPwzYtUgYp2KHvoI4agUchcqMc6oTmQEu/dx5/FetA=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="70"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="72be1489-6475-4245-8526-b055835c6787"><source><g id="379">Downloaded for Anonymous User (n/a) at Seoul National University Hospital from ClinicalKey.com by Elsevier on July 27, 2023. For personal use only. No other uses without permission. Copyright ©2023. Elsevier Inc. All rights reserved.</g><x id="380"/></source><seg-source><g id="379"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="110">Downloaded for Anonymous User (n/a) at Seoul National University Hospital from ClinicalKey.com by Elsevier on July 27, 2023.</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="111">For personal use only.</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="112">No other uses without permission.</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="113">Copyright ©2023.</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="114">Elsevier Inc. All rights reserved.</mrk></g><x id="380"/></seg-source><target><g id="379"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="110"/> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="111"/>