esshow modest improvements.</g></source><seg-source><g id="399"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="116">results,thepublishedbeforeandafterimagesshow modest improvements.</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="399"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="116"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="116"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">Ia5IaLXrRkFgqh8My7OkJl6Qk1mMfhca7m7VNXR8GZQ=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="73"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="0c6dbd04-7d26-4562-96ff-362d79dd2c6a"><source><g id="402">Non-Caucasian Ethnic Groups and Skin Types</g></source><seg-source><g id="402"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="117">Non-Caucasian Ethnic Groups and Skin Types</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="402"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="117"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="117"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">8IAM0U3WxwZMd/0SSNbpihYz0GRTSTEtiTEBVS1SlLo=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="74"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="2ab5c8ee-fd79-48ff-9bc3-d94010f5391c"><source><g id="409"><g id="405">Most studies were on Caucasian skin types.</g><g id="405"> </g><g id="405">Chan and colleagues</g><g id="408">11 </g><g id="412">reported on 49 Chinese patients with Fitzpatrick skin types III and IV followed for up to 6 months.</g><g id="412"> As in other studies, most patients had transient  erythema  and  edema.  Two  cases  of postinflammatory  hyperpigmentation  were  seen on the forehead at 1 month.</g></g></source><seg-source><g id="409"><g id="405"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="118">Most studies were on Caucasian skin types.</mrk></g><g id="405"> </g><mrk mtype="seg" mid="119"><g id="405">Chan and colleagues</g><g id="408">11 </g><g id="412">reported on 49 Chinese patients with Fitzpatrick skin types III and IV followed for up to 6 months.</g></mrk><g id="412"> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="120">As in other studies, most patients had transient  erythema  and  edema.</mrk>  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="121">Two  cases  of postinflammatory  hyperpigmentation  were  seen on the forehead at 1 month.</mrk></g></g></seg-source><target><g id="409"><g id="405"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="118"/></g><g id="405"> </g><mrk mtype="seg" mid="119"/><g id="412"> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="120"/>  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="121"/></g></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="118"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">inD0eIjF/3P8wZC/Y7KYvyDpnrIPDQWqK61WNCOhWrs=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="119"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">uMPlGIe/GAO4PxTS3BnYsI5Wd5wiaas7/SXT0FYcoEo=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="120"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">GHIJ/Bt6hG/MlUDYHO4YX3pXO+KGGWBfUWGSkCCStUw=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="121"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">i5NHwFH4ttT/KFhXrBPrhIlT36E0rwyJwawJ3tDPwUc=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="75"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="75e034cf-a0f1-403b-8c69-ba11c2e66990"><source><g id="419"><g id="415">Of 22 Korean patients with Fitzpatrick skin types III to VI treated with Ulthera, 2 developed whitish wheals  or  striations  but  no  further  details  were provided.</g><g id="418">4</g></g></source><seg-source><g id="419"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="122"><g id="415">Of 22 Korean patients with Fitzpatrick skin types III to VI treated with Ulthera, 2 developed whitish wheals  or  striations  but  no  further  details  were provided.</g><g id="418">4</g></mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="419"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="122"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="122"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">RFa0oTlH1op8yjV4LHWGs0QEtOMA2RQVlQ0n2j5zj/I=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="76"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="68a273fc-47e7-4285-a4cc-121a511fcbd5"><source><g id="422">Pain and Comfort Management</g></source><seg-source><g id="422"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="123">Pain and Comfort Management</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="422"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="123"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="123"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">uP6z4N91WwXZjfLbXSsOSFq7XK6WJZr67PYMhlxzErA=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="77"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="b34f5f56-f7b1-47cd-a157-44017d331b74"><source><g id="425">One  frequent  complaint  of  the  Ulthera  system is  pain  during  treatment.  Moderate  to  severe pain  may  limit  the  amount  of  energy  delivered, decrease   the   treatment   areas,   and   increase treatment   duration   times.   Topical   anesthetics can  provide  some  relief,  but  when  not  used, 54%  of  patients  reported  their  pain  as  being “severe.” Specific protocols for comfort manage-ment during treatment have not been developed but   the   following   options   are   available   and include:</g></source><seg-source><g id="425"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="124">One  frequent  complaint  of  the  Ulthera  system is  pain  during  treatment.</mrk>  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="125">Moderate  to  severe pain  may  limit  the  amount  of  energy  delivered, decrease   the   treatment   areas,   and   increase treatment   duration   times.</mrk>   <mrk mtype="seg" mid="126">Topical   anesthetics can  provide  some  relief,  but  when  not  used, 54%  of  patients  reported  their  pain  as  being “severe.”</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="127">Specific protocols for comfort manage-ment during treatment have not been developed but   the   following   options   are   available   and include:</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="425"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="124"/>  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="125"/>   <mrk mtype="seg" mid="126"/> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="127"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="124"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">rZ4OyNWITLSwH+twXioD12qASOLB2N8TuFa8bVI2+RE=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="125"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">aCb9dJkAKU68QCrK5YtGfk1/B93Zukx67KPsIrgOVaw=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="126"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">Mz0k2XBqyof0J1DtLeL3PW3BJw3w6IkTvGhRNfjjtEI=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="127"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">uyonj/Xqa4HrmnQMP/obP92pus7ZkpP7k2Y49fDDrYw=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="78"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="c738ab86-9fb4-4525-b5ae-ef039c3c9a4a"><source><g id="428">  Nitrous oxide gas</g></source><seg-source><g id="428">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="128">Nitrous oxide gas</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="428">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="128"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="128"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">iMSVtQlNU2iCe7bKIbRy4gwXKeDVh2hEOalW1J3lkOI=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="79"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="34181dde-2c83-49a6-a673-8cbbd7fc6a2f"><source><g id="431">  Oralnonsteroidalantiinflammatorymedications   Oral narcotics</g></source><seg-source><g id="431">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="129">Oralnonsteroidalantiinflammatorymedications   Oral narcotics</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="431">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="129"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="129"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">bENEonna0mnyw6AGSyzMXG7epITTUvQRw325ORcE9f0=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="80"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="f10eca9a-f33c-4c93-9740-7043fb74fb5d"><source><g id="434">  Oral anxiolytics</g></source><seg-source><g id="434">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="130">Oral anxiolytics</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="434">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="130"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="130"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">hAIOVWEpGCYJKrF1Y4ttA0LeBOtDTaey+y0AVd8Dt2M=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="81"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="55f3e242-f711-4a9b-ad64-ab1e4904a309"><source><g id="437">  Topical anesthetics</g></source><seg-source><g id="437">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="131">Topical anesthetics</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="437">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="131"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="131"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">WFSLMjtSQXTCGMWJPXo/jI20i4nmNRSXfQjBK9eBY7c=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="82"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="34fcb2cd-f4ea-4a8e-94c2-a07d02bcc189"><source><g id="440">  Injectable anesthetic nerve blocks   Distraction techniques</g></source><seg-source><g id="440">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="132">Injectable anesthetic nerve blocks   Distraction techniques</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="440">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="132"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="132"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">GbhfFL4th0/Bz8Y/zMqQaUFBoDY8j5akFPjkO5vTco0=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="83"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="b5817e3f-e214-49cd-993e-9397b26526d5"><source><g id="443">  Cool air devices and fans   Precooled ultrasound gel</g></source><seg-source><g id="443">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="133">Cool air devices and fans   Precooled ultrasound gel</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="443">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="133"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="133"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">WQYUkXdxUPhAy66cTLJM7yItesWAgxYLa+GJS1rL8QQ=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="84"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="0f20b8a0-0ab3-4c25-82c5-b01ccc142d69"><source><g id="446">These modalities may be used alone or in com-bination depending on patient tolerance and clin-ical judgment.</g></source><seg-source><g id="446"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="134">These modalities may be used alone or in com-bination depending on patient tolerance and clin-ical judgment.</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="446"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="134"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="134"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">j5k4cAAPnfd2VcViM9813WMxmZdmNkMOAIBbeu0steo=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="85"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="977947eb-951c-4b73-b180-9941cd96e71d"><source><g id="453"><g id="449">Based on small pilot trials,</g><g id="452">12  </g><g id="456">the following was found during Ulthera treatments:</g></g></source><seg-source><g id="453"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="135"><g id="449">Based on small pilot trials,</g><g id="452">12  </g><g id="456">the following was found during Ulthera treatments:</g></mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="453"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="135"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="135"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">ZWjZb/nnkrMp7zV+qmdsmc0Gu/scyhfCsCRU1jUjNfw=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="86"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="756c3986-c043-4743-b015-7d8b0bb7140e"><source><g id="459">  No difference in pain relief between 800 mg of ibuprofen versus 10 mg hydrocodone/500 mg acetaminophen   given   60   minutes   before treatment</g></source><seg-source><g id="459">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="136">No difference in pain relief between 800 mg of ibuprofen versus 10 mg hydrocodone/500 mg acetaminophen   given   60   minutes   before treatment</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="459">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="136"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="136"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">m7+QLOFrFr9rIncPetur2p+03LtwAWGCBKa+9kGUuPc=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="87"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="9ec54443-20fe-4d9b-bec0-3c5f96af0c01"><source><g id="462">  No  difference  in  pain  relief  between  topical liposomal lidocaine and a placebo control</g></source><seg-source><g id="462">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="137">No  difference  in  pain  relief  between  topical liposomal lidocaine and a placebo control</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="462">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="137"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="137"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">sNxHakhN15EP+4hil4dnUAu5kjkd60IypltMSs7ilJw=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="88"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="5ff70715-9cee-412c-bc14-7e8f24b3ac51"><source><g id="465">  Lower   energy   treatment   levels   had   less discomfort that higher energy levels without a difference in clinical outcome at 180 days</g></source><seg-source><g id="465">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="138">Lower   energy   treatment   levels   had   less discomfort that higher energy levels without a difference in clinical outcome at 180 days</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="465">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="138"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="138"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">kXdTGh/lUU4wfoNDs1OqjE0BBWdA5gMU1Keyb53tv6I=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="89"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="af2d6725-f685-4ff4-b554-55c723e15986"><source><g id="468">Although inflammation is a necessary component of  neocollagenesis  after  Ulthera  treatment,  it  is</g></source><seg-source><g id="468"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="139">Although inflammation is a necessary component of  neocollagenesis  after  Ulthera  treatment,  it  is</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="468"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="139"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="139"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">wA1uFHt7NoG0YkCxu1dKBgfY7mhjKVIHq8E4teIC4LI=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="90"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="9ce5b38b-6770-4fa6-a93f-108d7ec32a17"><source><x id="469"/><g id="472">unknown if chronic nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory medicationusemayinterferewiththefinaloutcome.</g></source><seg-source><mrk mtype="seg" mid="140"><x id="469"/><g id="472">unknown if chronic nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory medicationusemayinterferewiththefinaloutcome.</g></mrk></seg-source><target><mrk mtype="seg" mid="140"/></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="140"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">5X4cGIVZZPaenNlHjMZTXoFarVSFLqUwfo2LkbD2iVQ=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="91"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="d573ca0e-7cb1-4cc8-a8e5-a5e15fe4d17d"><source><g id="475">Recovery and Down Time</g></source><seg-source><g id="475"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="141">Recovery and Down Time</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="475"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="141"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="141"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">SltU2DuvjGk+yYJpVFpIZmYMz9SUbUvssrlrouWF5Vs=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="92"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="4a8133e6-8ac5-495d-84d2-3f517e9b30cb"><source><g id="478">Other  than  the  mild  tissue  reactions  described elsewhere in this paper, the Ulthera system can be considered to have no down time and a minimal recovery period. No specific aftercare is needed.</g></source><seg-source><g id="478"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="142">Other  than  the  mild  tissue  reactions  described elsewhere in this paper, the Ulthera system can be considered to have no down time and a minimal recovery period.</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="143">No specific aftercare is needed.</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="478"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="142"/> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="143"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="142"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">2YyHQCPOJCrbOD/jb7FhGsckuzmlCU+MePYS9r7SB24=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="143"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">HdBn0fFub4uyGTERTB9KVD1M7YqiGZpLqyO7KZPnpUo=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="93"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="ee2d07b7-f3ba-4860-8124-dda550347233"><source><g id="481">Side Effects and Complications</g></source><seg-source><g id="481"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="144">Side Effects and Complications</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="481"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="144"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="144"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">V9mj2ClvJTrABicyrPlzjEMu2bVytv1vScLzgLs6EYo=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="94"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="13eb612d-1b51-46cc-b25b-3e90231b409e"><source><g id="488"><g id="484">Most  published  studies  reported  only  mild  side effects,  typically  mild  erythema  and  edema  that usually resolves after 2 days but no longer than 7 days.</g><g id="487">6  </g><g id="491">However, some patients reported tran-sient bruising, skin pigment changes,</g><g id="494">9 </g><g id="497">and neuro-pathic pain for up to 3 months, after treatment.</g><g id="497"> </g><g id="497">A small group of patients also reported numbness of  the  jawline,  which  resolved  within  3  weeks.</g><g id="500">4 </g><g id="503">A review of the literature focusing on the safety of MFU confirmed that side effects are generally mild and transient in nature.</g><g id="506">13</g></g></source><seg-source><g id="488"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="145"><g id="484">Most  published  studies  reported  only  mild  side effects,  typically  mild  erythema  and  edema  that usually resolves after 2 days but no longer than 7 days.</g><g id="487">6  </g><g id="491">However, some patients reported tran-sient bruising, skin pigment changes,</g><g id="494">9 </g><g id="497">and neuro-pathic pain for up to 3 months, after treatment.</g></mrk><g id="497"> </g><mrk mtype="seg" mid="146"><g id="497">A small group of patients also reported numbness of  the  jawline,  which  resolved  within  3  weeks.</g><g id="500">4 </g><g id="503">A review of the literature focusing on the safety of MFU confirmed that side effects are generally mild and transient in nature.</g><g id="506">13</g></mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="488"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="145"/><g id="497"> </g><mrk mtype="seg" mid="146"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="145"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">6UPz+AbQVUZB2Lq6KpwD/G0EHtY7ouNIycoZtu54yFY=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="146"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">N0LQRZOyo1oiVt8dSyUtGiDXfr9HtNQlMdGNNdRmcsk=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="95"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="38cba10e-1267-49dd-86bb-a54b3f71a8f6"><source><g id="509">RESULTS</g></source><seg-source><g id="509"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="147">RESULTS</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="509"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="147"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="147"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">CcH5zGOprnhzvfbrHOXaItez4JU6KB9vKfgdqwonTEo=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="96"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="3e8470b0-3d77-4051-ae68-26338b7b2499"><source><g id="516"><g id="512">Collagen contraction immediately after treatment may result in an initial tissue “lift.” There is also mild edema that contributes to the early aesthetic improvement seen by patients. However, the heat-induced  collagen  synthesis  and  remodeling  can persist for up to 1 year.</g><g id="512"> </g><g id="512">A typical result is shown in </g><g id="515">Fig. 3</g><g id="519">.</g><g id="519"> Because ideal candidates tend to have mild to moderate aging, those with more severe aging, sagging skin, and platysmal bands are likely to be better served by surgical treatment.</g></g></source><seg-source><g id="516"><g id="512"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="148">Collagen contraction immediately after treatment may result in an initial tissue “lift.”</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="149">There is also mild edema that contributes to the early aesthetic improvement seen by patients.</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="150">However, the heat-induced  collagen  synthesis  and  remodeling  can persist for up to 1 year.</mrk></g><g id="512"> </g><mrk mtype="seg" mid="151"><g id="512">A typical result is shown in </g><g id="515">Fig. 3</g><g id="519">.</g></mrk><g id="519"> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="152">Because ideal candidates tend to have mild to moderate aging, those with more severe aging, sagging skin, and platysmal bands are likely to be better served by surgical treatment.</mrk></g></g></seg-source><target><g id="516"><g id="512"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="148"/> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="149"/> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="150"/></g><g id="512"> </g><mrk mtype="seg" mid="151"/><g id="519"> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="152"/></g></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="148"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">jabTXTMwXU1r00fTRP9KXyQeQegbn9hMSxIkPWmICtA=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="149"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">rNOLowjnpvlHT20mJBOFTvkBZ4zzLwM1KxvkIi/te4U=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="150"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">Gm4gUC4xHPwKRtoI+t4G0QqZxQ+AP4rxNto5rMKYpYY=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="151"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">s9g5xP/PUNXyUkSPmrVApe4O7T9N5ND3EJCwv6xzxPw=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="152"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">d/XKxjShe5zJdoF2ylNI0ZELDl2VTV35HPiRGevgED0=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="97"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="96895b73-c669-4dd9-8889-7f5ff4143c78"><source><g id="526"><g id="522">As with any noninvasive aesthetic treatment, not all  patients  and  clinicians  see  an  improvement. A 2010 study by Ulthera, 51 of 70 patients (73%) had  a  quantitative  improvement  in  tissue  lift  in the submental areas after 3 months. Of those 51 patients,   84%   (43   patients)   had   a   qualitative improvement as determined by blinded assessors. Therefore, the overall positive response was 61%. Overall patient satisfaction was 67%. Because the energy density settings were about one-half of the density  recommended,  it  is  likely  that  a  higher response is possible if more aggressive treatment protocols are used. A follow-up study of 64 pa-tients  found  64%  to  79%  of  patients  reporting some  degree  of  improvement  between  2  and 6 months after treatment.</g><g id="522"> </g><g id="522">The group that included jowl treatment had lower satisfaction scores.</g><g id="525">14</g></g></source><seg-source><g id="526"><g id="522"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="153">As with any noninvasive aesthetic treatment, not all  patients  and  clinicians  see  an  improvement.</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="154">A 2010 study by Ulthera, 51 of 70 patients (73%) had  a  quantitative  improvement  in  tissue  lift  in the submental areas after 3 months.</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="155">Of those 51 patients,   84%   (43   patients)   had   a   qualitative improvement as determined by blinded assessors.</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="156">Therefore, the overall positive response was 61%.</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="157">Overall patient satisfaction was 67%.</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="158">Because the energy density settings were about one-half of the density  recommended,  it  is  likely  that  a  higher response is possible if more aggressive treatment protocols are used.</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="159">A follow-up study of 64 pa-tients  found  64%  to  79%  of  patients  reporting some  degree  of  improvement  between  2  and 6 months after treatment.</mrk></g><g id="522"> </g><mrk mtype="seg" mid="160"><g id="522">The group that included jowl treatment had lower satisfaction scores.</g><g id="525">14</g></mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="526"><g id="522"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="153"/> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="154"/> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="155"/> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="156"/> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="157"/> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="158"/> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="159"/></g><g id="522"> </g><mrk mtype="seg" mid="160"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="153"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">Au1sAxngrv2u6h/SWq90OJBdr1x1hSJGJ45o/4DSnRg=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="154"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">nNr9KK0dIQlDWvpU0QFBShf2lXutTzUl39OR7YiuBrE=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="155"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">SMe3CvflC5YhG0f0eXeTsI0up0QHr8DcmSS9jQsN1ak=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="156"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">1jFZQLpC8Vb3SOb7h6GLaEieYLL+tsnsBV7drzEGp+w=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="157"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">u9VsZHIW/+J+sIqcSNDf+oGCKEEmfVpsSQMu7m1qAII=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="158"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">1nuY6+sEGVa5/dS0uBmzwfoTnC6mnlnuh/CBFsKwlUc=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="159"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">C4Gc8kicd82CFXy6CDu9muTq74xPIb47k9y/qVrKR+0=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="160"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">EukPDmBZFFmwIbd12EQ35ncurVtwTCbbIgZ99tXksFU=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="98"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="d0cf5e58-b058-430f-8021-9a9e25e1455f"><source><g id="533"><g id="529">One  independent  study</g><g id="532">15   </g><g id="536">of  10  patients  with standardized  photography  and  blinded,  experi-enced  clinician  evaluators  found  that  2  of  the patients (20%) did not show any improvement.</g><g id="536"> Pa-tient self-assessment found 1 patient (10%) who</g></g></source><seg-source><g id="533"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="161"><g id="529">One  independent  study</g><g id="532">15   </g><g id="536">of  10  patients  with standardized  photography  and  blinded,  experi-enced  clinician  evaluators  found  that  2  of  the patients (20%) did not show any improvement.</g></mrk><g id="536"> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="162">Pa-tient self-assessment found 1 patient (10%) who</mrk></g></g></seg-source><target><g id="533"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="161"/><g id="536"> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="162"/></g></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="161"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">h/axgB+TF4eOjAnGTlkxEYJibuD/ttwqXotYlHS9tWU=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="162"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">Vf4YIIXtPacndtuPmZqOsaI9uUsi8L2FC4ZTNMkCgIo=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="99"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="1e65d314-29fa-403c-8a4b-f28b9babe462"><source><g id="539">Downloaded for Anonymous User (n/a) at Seoul National University Hospital from ClinicalKey.com by Elsevier on July 27, 2023. For personal use only. No other uses without permission. Copyright ©2023. Elsevier Inc. All rights reserved.</g><x id="540"/></source><seg-source><g id="539"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="163">Downloaded for Anonymous User (n/a) at Seoul National University Hospital from ClinicalKey.com by Elsevier on July 27, 2023.</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="164">For personal use only.</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="165">No other uses without permission.</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="166">Copyright ©2023.</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="167">Elsevier Inc. All rights reserved.</mrk></g><x id="540"/></seg-source><target><g id="539"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="163"/> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="164"/> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="165"/> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="166"/> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="167"/></g><x id="540"/></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="163"><sdl:rep id="mTircHggKyN0qYacONQdEAcyLynKpWXg+eutC8ezjvI="/><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">mTircHggKyN0qYacONQdEAcyLynKpWXg+eutC8ezjvI=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="164"><sdl:rep id="apFJZlrHl140uoajSp2UIdNk88J2FSPtQVN3Gsm8Z/8="/><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">apFJZlrHl140uoajSp2UIdNk88J2FSPtQVN3Gsm8Z/8=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="165"><sdl:rep id="P3yAfTJ3Db4SFDuoEejStQdX0TywfhOhIcA9JmgaltM="/><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">P3yAfTJ3Db4SFDuoEejStQdX0TywfhOhIcA9JmgaltM=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="166"><sdl:rep id="UtaULUqG/A/LJLccCi54FYXwHaD9yQDeWghC7okUl/c="/><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">UtaULUqG/A/LJLccCi54FYXwHaD9yQDeWghC7okUl/c=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="167"><sdl:rep id="ebZCJya3RmLgEZAXDuPo359W5RHKGXhy1Hb6+bl3SnY="/><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">ebZCJya3RmLgEZAXDuPo359W5RHKGXhy1Hb6+bl3SnY=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="100"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="55861ddf-8c5a-471f-ad2f-637b04657631"><source><x id="541"/><x id="542"/><g id="552"><g id="545">Microfocused Ultrasound for Skin Tightening	</g><g id="551">581</g></g><x id="553"/><x id="554"/><x id="555"/><x id="556"/></source><seg-source><x id="541"/><mrk mtype="seg" mid="168"><x id="542"/><g id="552"><g id="545">Microfocused Ultrasound for Skin Tightening	</g><g id="551">581</g></g><x id="553"/><x id="554"/><x id="555"/><x id="556"/></mrk></seg-source><target><x id="541"/><mrk mtype="seg" mid="168"/></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="168"><sdl:rep id="j+A08L+4G/xtXwALuYZ/RZcoqtLI9bpgvaQrb+YUjZQ="/><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">j+A08L+4G/xtXwALuYZ/RZcoqtLI9bpgvaQrb+YUjZQ=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="101"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="662efc5c-5d85-4da7-a0eb-6e139f81ddae"><source><g id="563"><g id="559">Fig. 3.  </g><g id="562">A 45-year-old woman before (left) and after (right) ulthera treatment of lower face and submental region.</g></g></source><seg-source><g id="563"><g id="559"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="169">Fig. 3.</mrk>  </g><g id="562"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="170">A 45-year-old woman before (left) and after (right) ulthera treatment of lower face and submental region.</mrk></g></g></seg-source><target><g id="563"><g id="559"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="169"/>  </g><g id="562"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="170"/></g></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="169"><sdl:rep id="LjHbAc+m+xVrLWU5bTE2pGR6uBtWi12RCfNGOOp/WYA="/><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">LjHbAc+m+xVrLWU5bTE2pGR6uBtWi12RCfNGOOp/WYA=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="170"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">xhPbFY9TjBFsL4rPHxVZ4hIYoiDgNA/y1hM5X3Na2tU=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="102"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="8d2f4065-fe2b-4863-bffd-0119663aedeb"><source><g id="566">reported  no  improvement  and  2  patients  (20%) who  reported  only  mild  improvement.  However, treatment protocols, the amount of energy deliv-ered, and individual patient factors make general-izations  on  expected  outcomes  difficult.  Older patients  with  less  “healing  potential”  may  not respond as well as younger patients.</g></source><seg-source><g id="566"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="171">reported  no  improvement  and  2  patients  (20%) who  reported  only  mild  improvement.</mrk>  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="172">However, treatment protocols, the amount of energy deliv-ered, and individual patient factors make general-izations  on  expected  outcomes  difficult.</mrk>  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="173">Older patients  with  less  “healing  potential”  may  not respond as well as younger patients.</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="566"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="171"/>  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="172"/>  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="173"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="171"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">Rhsi+zAEjgiIGav78DDKDyiUX289Y4MLEiJCcErM0BE=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="172"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">nQyLWF04Qek/+guzTXVnW7eJd1vYlWq21266ZR8WI/8=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="173"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">K3ImttiO8tMFapFVGwtWOmtNnOc+7bnCqIgFLPEzu4U=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="103"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="f101e43f-49e3-4fdd-b237-5e44db4ba61d"><source><g id="573"><g id="569">In  the  largest  Ulthera  sponsored  study  with qualitative    and    quantitative    imaging    assess-ment,</g><g id="572">16  </g><g id="580"><g id="576">58% of 93 patients had improvement in skin  laxity  after  3  months,  as  determined  by blinded reviewers.</g></g><g id="580"><g id="576"> </g><g id="576">In patients with a body mass in-dex of greater than 30 kg/m</g><g id="579">2</g><g id="583">, 55% of patients did not   have   a   change,   compared   with   12%   of patients  with  a  body  mass  index  of  30  mg/kg</g><g id="586">2 </g><g id="589">or   less.</g><g id="589">   At   the   same   time,   66%   of   patients perceived  an  improvement in skin laxity  of their lower  half  of  the  face  and  neck.  All  patients received   a   superficial   and   deep   treatment   of approximately 295 lines. It is possible that a higher treatment density (more lines) and assessment at 6 to 9 months may have shown more favorable responses.</g></g></g></source><seg-source><g id="573"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="174"><g id="569">In  the  largest  Ulthera  sponsored  study  with qualitative    and    quantitative    imaging    assess-ment,</g><g id="572">16  </g><g id="580"><g id="576">58% of 93 patients had improvement in skin  laxity  after  3  months,  as  determined  by blinded reviewers.</g></g></mrk><g id="580"><g id="576"> </g><mrk mtype="seg" mid="175"><g id="576">In patients with a body mass in-dex of greater than 30 kg/m</g><g id="579">2</g><g id="583">, 55% of patients did not   have   a   change,   compared   with   12%   of patients  with  a  body  mass  index  of  30  mg/kg</g><g id="586">2 </g><g id="589">or   less.</g></mrk><g id="589">   <mrk mtype="seg" mid="176">At   the   same   time,   66%   of   patients perceived  an  improvement in skin laxity  of their lower  half  of  the  face  and  neck.</mrk>  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="177">All  patients received   a   superficial   and   deep   treatment   of approximately 295 lines.</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="178">It is possible that a higher treatment density (more lines) and assessment at 6 to 9 months may have shown more favorable responses.</mrk></g></g></g></seg-source><target><g id="573"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="174"/><g id="580"><g id="576"> </g><mrk mtype="seg" mid="175"/><g id="589">   <mrk mtype="seg" mid="176"/>  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="177"/> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="178"/></g></g></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="174"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">eIeuCwnQDorSyVYNfq5VJe3FG78zA4MvfOEkWzeyHmk=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="175"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">mjKaeihcAdvbxARwssZu5MKl9M3hERgGkakcurvIQ1E=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="176"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">N11qS4/2gGKSJnRlYmsTrs1jOmDkVmhaIVLb1ghyUIA=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="177"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">KSYwcQeB4rTT1DdGYIadAL1iychwDIN/gLUtZNJ99aI=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="178"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">aWyUwZPgDpIYWBHwjnlyiMEhqxQ05llsC5Gw4xNoICg=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="104"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="66d62593-1f3d-4b68-b019-cd7675f58fb1"><source><g id="592">Duration of Results</g></source><seg-source><g id="592"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="179">Duration of Results</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="592"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="179"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="179"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">CU8+UZwADtGDWWDs80sa+Xep6tJOfWepKxqls1nTAa4=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="105"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="90e8133c-e5f7-4aee-b44e-c3b676f88753"><source><g id="595">Although no skin tightening procedure can claim permanent  results,  the  long-term  outcomes  of energy-derived skin tightening devices is lacking. Surgical procedures (face and neck lifts), however, have demonstrated continued improvement at up to 10 years.</g></source><seg-source><g id="595"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="180">Although no skin tightening procedure can claim permanent  results,  the  long-term  outcomes  of energy-derived skin tightening devices is lacking.</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="181">Surgical procedures (face and neck lifts), however, have demonstrated continued improvement at up to 10 years.</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="595"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="180"/> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="181"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="180"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">xl/0f3KBxAdUYzDL2CezzMueuazwbMSacXd4VHdgWJE=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="181"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">zDjSq4CrnUVu9YL4aozNBCR80RwVkrFHEfQk7dp0Jmw=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="106"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="7eaedd99-91c2-42df-9325-35041ea30870"><source><g id="598">Physician Oversight</g></source><seg-source><g id="598"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="182">Physician Oversight</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="598"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="182"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="182"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">dODy3+ErOGoefFffz8U0qUs0VPgmCz6oB+b6CE73xfQ=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="107"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="c390964a-420c-47e9-ab47-b9f13102e6db"><source><g id="601">Physicians may administer the treatments them-selves,   but   in   most   cases,   nurses   or   trained aestheticians  provide  the  service.  Specifics  of oversight regarding patient evaluation and physi-cian availability vary according to local regulations.</g></source><seg-source><g id="601"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="183">Physicians may administer the treatments them-selves,   but   in   most   cases,   nurses   or   trained aestheticians  provide  the  service.</mrk>  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="184">Specifics  of oversight regarding patient evaluation and physi-cian availability vary according to local regulations.</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="601"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="183"/>  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="184"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="183"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">kBqp8S5Yid/85otgpPmPHig/qihktbceK0be44n67ns=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="184"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">hbqZBR4A9FZIEUuzrki5w/JMtWPnBPmWAx3gjJaSb70=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="108"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="9b5a0020-85ee-4413-be7d-0a3b87e63cc9"><source><x id="602"/><g id="605">TREATMENT PROTOCOL VARIATION</g></source><seg-source><mrk mtype="seg" mid="185"><x id="602"/><g id="605">TREATMENT PROTOCOL VARIATION</g></mrk></seg-source><target><mrk mtype="seg" mid="185"/></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="185"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">HDspUbAAzI2a5LRicwf8iJc5sdIVd2oPpPwhLyNJZB0=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="109"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="0f4c8366-c339-4c81-8106-a822350c98f6"><source><g id="612"><g id="608">Because not all patients may not respond to treat-ments, there is room for increasing the treatment line density. Experienced Ulthera user consensus group participants reported high rates of efficacy when using 600 to 800 lines per treatment.</g><g id="608"> </g><g id="608">Treat-ment  densities  of  up  to  1500  lines  have  been used, but there seems to be little clinical return after  1200  to  1500  lines.</g><g id="611">17   </g><g id="615">Therefore,  physician assessment and a patient-specific treatment plan should be done for each patient.</g></g></source><seg-source><g id="612"><g id="608"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="186">Because not all patients may not respond to treat-ments, there is room for increasing the treatment line density.</mrk> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="187">Experienced Ulthera user consensus group participants reported high rates of efficacy when using 600 to 800 lines per treatment.</mrk></g><g id="608"> </g><mrk mtype="seg" mid="188"><g id="608">Treat-ment  densities  of  up  to  1500  lines  have  been used, but there seems to be little clinical return after  1200  to  1500  lines.</g><g id="611">17   </g><g id="615">Therefore,  physician assessment and a patient-specific treatment plan should be done for each patient.</g></mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="612"><g id="608"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="186"/> <mrk mtype="seg" mid="187"/></g><g id="608"> </g><mrk mtype="seg" mid="188"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="186"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">qYoxx6Xai9KfPHGcS1fh99Lfr9S+a74GjrpSjcyLpog=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="187"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">rsNd9jR+3RCdu52uNzWeiqFcIChXHk9cH2l88+F3MgA=</sdl:value></sdl:seg><sdl:seg id="188"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">B68g9T8++4LW0l01OVoYwHFOGIf8LozAbZRgA9rNcTw=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="110"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="54251e20-3820-4b42-8167-b1a96c96b991"><source><g id="618">Other Treatment Options</g></source><seg-source><g id="618"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="189">Other Treatment Options</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="618"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="189"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="189"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">AcAfK/29K9EX+SgLkrU+PuLEYAMcyKWm1glwxKyp5qw=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="111"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="881b7211-1c66-457b-b7a0-9efe57b5e93e"><source><g id="621">Ulthera is only 1 option in the facial rejuvenation armamentarium.</g></source><seg-source><g id="621"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="190">Ulthera is only 1 option in the facial rejuvenation armamentarium.</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="621"><mrk mtype="seg" mid="190"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="190"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">kDfF+JpArg/NmpB12Fv3koFB/FOOHtR6uJtBwQsSvs8=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="112"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="c1424a7c-34f8-4195-b7b9-fe60fa188dfa"><source><g id="624">  Brow elevation can be achieved with neuro-modulators and injectable fillers</g></source><seg-source><g id="624">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="191">Brow elevation can be achieved with neuro-modulators and injectable fillers</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="624">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="191"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="191"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">vi8O8nn3zrW4cj9ZzNtDyaRrC+mainC7B4KOv/m0cYk=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="113"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="9333e2d3-aacc-471c-8b62-5c7f6e2ec8c8"><source><g id="627">  Facial and neck skin tightening can also be achieved  by  a  variety  of  energy  devices, including RF</g></source><seg-source><g id="627">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="192">Facial and neck skin tightening can also be achieved  by  a  variety  of  energy  devices, including RF</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="627">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="192"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="192"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">9eJqf4ukIl5BGFd71R9j3MQ5qfsKrEtjKJQAAxtR2es=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="114"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="1d6442e7-179f-4305-9426-ad47875d3900"><source><g id="630">  Injectable fillers and fat grafts can result in mid and lower face elevation</g></source><seg-source><g id="630">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="193">Injectable fillers and fat grafts can result in mid and lower face elevation</mrk></g></seg-source><target><g id="630">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="193"/></g></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="193"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">N+yfwhmC9RmWoZpj/Iv+tvF6oGjWDLOhhyTIB7d9x/8=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="115"/><sdl:cxt id="2"/></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="d595bc6b-e4be-4370-8e2d-2579f52aeddd"><source><g id="633">  Lower facial skin laxity and jowls have been treated	with	conservative	laser-assisted liposuction</g></source><seg-source><g id="633">  <mrk mtype="seg" mid="194">Lower facial skin laxity and jowls have been treated	with	conservative	laser-assisted liposuction</mr